; Test for issue #3182: commodity names longer than 255 bytes used to
; produce a misleading "Quoted commodity symbol lacks closing quote"
; error because the istream parser used a fixed 255-byte buffer.  The
; buffer has been replaced with a dynamic string, so quoted commodity
; symbols of arbitrary length now parse correctly.  A long bare symbol
; (one whose characters are all valid in unquoted form) is also no
; longer silently truncated at 255 bytes.

2026-04-25 quoted long commodity
    Assets:Holdings   1 "...................................................................................................................................................................................................................................................................."
    Assets:Cash      $-2

2026-04-25 bare long commodity
    Assets:Other      1 
    Assets:Cash      $-3

test commodities
"...................................................................................................................................................................................................................................................................."
$

end test
